1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of residual networks for image classification tasks using the ImageNet dataset. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of low-precision representation of deep neural networks and the trade-off between accuracy and compute. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for image classification tasks. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible as the paper discusses the use of deep neural networks and the concept of residual connections. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of sparse ternary connections in the network.
